[[File:TenelKa1.jpg|thumb|right|200px|The Hapan Royal Princess tiara featured enough rainbow gems to buy a solar system.]]
'''Rainbow gems''' were brilliant treasures that were not actually gems, but [[Silicon/Legends|silicon]]-based lifeforms native to the planet [[Gallinore]].

They matured only after thousands of years, and the glow they produced was caused by their inner light. Despite their biologic nature, rainbow gems could be used as [[Lightsaber crystal/Legends|lightsaber crystals]]. [[Tenel Ka Djo]], the [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] of [[Hapes/Legends|Hapes]], had a tiara of rainbow gems worth the price of an entire solar system. She used some of the crystals in her second lightsaber, after her first one malfunctioned and exploded, which also led to the loss of her arm.

The gems, often used in medallions, were considered very valuable, as just one was worth the price of a [[Mon Calamari Star Cruiser/Legends|Calamarian cruiser]]. Due to their great value and untraceable nature, these gems comprised part of a [[Huttese/Legends|Huttese]] bribe to [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Winstel Greelanx]] to purchase the battle plans for his [[Battle of Nar Shaddaa (4 BBY)|impending assault]] on [[Nar Shaddaa/Legends|Nar Shaddaa]]. The [[Huttese/Legends|Huttese]] bribe of gemstones was delivered by the young [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]].

